-----------
TUTORIAL 08
-----------

This is an introduction to bare-metal programming on Raspberry Pi using
C language. This module shows how to utilize the video graphics using frame
buffers. The ARM core needs to communicate with the GPU core through a
mailbox.

---------
Objective
---------

1- To understand how video graphics interface can be implemented
2- To understand how mailbox communications between ARM-VC work.

----------
Background
----------

--------
Contents
--------

All codes required to communicate using the mailbox is in 'main.c'.

Some assembly codes are required to create memory barrier.

